history.content: You should be fine. 61C doesn't depend on 61AB very much.

children.subject: From what I've seen, most students take 70 before or concurrently with 61C -- I wouldn't worry about "breaking" the series.

history.content:
Hi, I am currently a freshman who has taken 61A, Math 53, and is currently taking Physics 7A, 61B, and 16A.

If I were to take CS70 (instead of 61C) next semester, would it not be advisable (since its a break in the 61 series)? I am planning to take 16B next semester, so I thought it would be better to spread my classes and not focus too much on hardware if I took 61C also with 16B. 

Also, if I were to skip Physics 7B next semester and take it sophomore first year, would the break in the Physics series be harder?
history.subject: breaking 61 series with cs70?
